{"title":"Ride1Up Prodigy V2 Delivers Gates Belt Driven Mid-Motor Under $3K","link":"https://bikerumor.com/ride1up-prodigy-v2-delivers-gates-belt-driven-mid-motor-under-3k/","date":1695649686000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1533\" height=\"1157\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-0.jpg\" alt=\"ride1up prodigy v2 commuter e-bike with gates belt drive\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-0.jpg 1533w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-0-297x224.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-0-800x604.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-0-120x91.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-0-768x580.jpg 768w\" /></p>\n<p>Ride1Up’s e-bike catalog is almost entirely driven by hub motors and under $2,000, sometimes way under. The Prodigy is their sole mid-motor option, and the new Prodigy V2 gets some serious upgrades with a Gates Carbon Belt Drive and Brose mid-motor for just $2,695.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But it doesn’t stop there…the Enviolo rear hub has a CVT for seamless, stepless “gear changes”. Combined, it and the belt drive should make for a low-maintenance drivetrain full of name-brand parts from solid manufacturers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Prodigy V2 powertrain details</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-4.jpg\" alt=\"gates belt drive closeup\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-4.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-4-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-4-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Brose TF Sprinter motor puts out 90Nm of torque and assists up to 28mph (Class 3). Estimated range is 30-50 miles from the 36V14ah battery. They don’t list the watt-hour rating, but it’s 504Wh (because 36V x 14ah = 504wh).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-3.jpg\" alt=\"gates belt drive and brose motor closeup\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-3.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-3-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-2.jpg\" alt=\"enviolo cvt rear hub shifter and display\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-2.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Unlike most of their other bikes, this one doesn’t have a throttle, it only assists your own pedaling efforts. There are four assist modes and a full-color display to show them off, along with your speed and distance.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As for UL certification, their rep says that while the entire bike as a whole hasn’t been inspected by a UL lab, “the batteries and the charger along with the electrical systems are all UL-certified and compliant.”</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Other Specs &amp; Details</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-6.jpg\" alt=\"ride1up prodigy v2 commuter e-bike riding across the street\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-6.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-6-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-6-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Prodigy V2’s frame is alloy, with standard and step-through options. It only comes in one size, but they should fit riders from about 5’4″ thru 6’3″.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-5.jpg\" alt=\"ride1up prodigy v2 commuter e-bike with gates belt drive\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-5.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-5-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It comes with a 100mm travel air-sprung suspension fork, Tektro hydraulic disc brake with 180mm rotors, and alloy fenders front and rear. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-1.jpg\" alt=\"ride1up prodigy v2 commuter e-bike with gates belt drive\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-1.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-1-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The bike has front and rear lights, with an 80 Lux headlight with a daytime running mode. The rear light doubles as a brake light and is integrated into the rear rack. The rack can support up to 40lbs and they offer a variety of accessories for it, but it should also work with any standard pannier bags, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-9.jpg\" alt=\"ride1up prodigy v2 commuter e-bike with gates belt drive\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-9.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-9-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-9-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-9-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-9-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-9-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-7.jpg\" alt=\"ride1up prodigy v2 commuter e-bike with gates belt drive\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-7.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-7-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-7-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-7-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-7-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-7-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It rolls on basic wheels, but they’re wrapped in Maxxis Rekon Race 27.5×2.25″ tires. Complete bike weights range from 58-61lbs, and all versions are rated for a 300lb rider plus cargo weight limit.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-8.jpg\" alt=\"ride1up prodigy v2 commuter e-bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-8.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-8-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-8-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-8-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-8-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ride1up-prodigy-v2-commuter-ebike-belt-drive-brose-8-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s also a chain-driven model with a MicroSHIFT  Advent 9-speed derailleur/shifter, a Shimano Alivio 11-34 cassette, and a KMC chain. It’s $300 less at $2,395.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://ride1up.com/product/prodigy-v2/\" target=\"_blank\">Ride1up.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/ride1up-prodigy-v2-delivers-gates-belt-driven-mid-motor-under-3k/\">Ride1Up Prodigy V2 Delivers Gates Belt Driven Mid-Motor Under $3K</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"141546c18f3f5b25afc6c66795283c2285e906f78604f1a107c8f19a341bbf10","category":"Cycling"}